          "text": "Let me review the C version of task 4 (filter by radius).\n\n**Structure:**\n- Lines 10-12: `setvbuf(stdout, NULL, _IOFBF, 4096)` — fully buffered output, flush on return ✓\n- Lines 15-40: argument validation (argc, parse r, finite check, positive check) ✓\n- Lines 43-46: local variables\n- Lines 50-107: main loop\n- Lines 110-114: empty check at end\n\n**Issues:**\n\n1. **`free(s)` at lines 56-57, 61-62, 67-68 — logic bug.** Notice lines 56-57 (before the `if (ferror(stdin))` check):\n```c\nif (len == -1) {\n    free(s);\n    s = NULL;\n    if (ferror(stdin)) {\n        fprintf(stderr, \"Ошибка в IO\\n\");\n        /*free(s);\n        s = NULL;*/\n        return io_fail;\n    }\n    else {\n        /*free(s);\n        s = NULL;*/\n        break;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe `free(s); s = NULL;` is done BEFORE the ferror check, and then inside both branches `free(s)` and `s = NULL` are commented out. So `free(s)` is done once, set to NULL, then both branches check ferror or not. This is actually correct behavior — `free(s)` is done once before the branching.\n\nBut the remaining commented code (`/*free(s); s = NULL;*/`) is dead code that should be cleaned up. Not a bug, but messy.\n\n2. **`ctr` placement (line 98):** `++ctr` is AFTER the error check and BEFORE the radius filter check. This is for counting ALL parsed points. The check at line 110: `if (ctr == 0)` → `no_input`. This verifies that at least one point was entered.\n\nBUT if points are entered but none pass the filter, `ctr > 0`, no output, returns 0. Same behavior as the C++ version. ✓\n\n3. **`sqrt(p.x * p.x + ...) < r` at line 101** — uses `sqrt` from `<math.h>`. ✓\n\n4. **Missing `free(s)` at line 112:** At line 110-114:\n```c\nif (ctr == 0) {\n    fprintf(stderr, \"Точек не обнаружено\\n\");\n    free(s);    // s is already NULL from the last iteration\n    return no_input;\n}\n```\n\n`s` was freed and set to NULL at line 105-106 in the last iteration. Then EOF is hit, `len == -1`, and we